=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How would you design the WAR epic quest weapon?</span><hr size=1> Well I've seen most of the opinions of the Warrior epic quest weapon stats, and most people have agreed that they are disappointed in the stats, especially after all the trouble you have to go through to get the weapons.  So then I figured, what would be our ideal weapon stats?  Well, what do you all think?<br>
<br>
Here's what I would like to wield:<br>
<br>
Ratio: Not the best but it needs to be faster.  Take the damage down to 12 from 14, but lower the delay to 20, so you'll have a pair of 12/20 1H slashers.<br>
<br>
AC: Each weapon should have 10 or 15 AC, which is compareable to other desirable weapons we can use which have AC on them.<br>
<br>
The Proc: Stun with DD.  70 or so points of DD accompanied with a stun as the proc on BOTH weapons.<br>
<br>
So there you have it, a set of the best stun proc weapons in the game, and probably the best way for a warrior to keep the attention of the mob, as well as gain 20 to 30 AC by wielding these weapons in order to deal with that abuse.<br>
<br>
As for the 2H, I'd probably never use it so I'm not sure on what I'd want in a 2H. <p><img src="http://www.eqrealms.com/dantes_sig.jpg" width="260" height="137"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 736<br> <font color=#CC9900>(10/23/00 3:06:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How would you design the WAR epic quest weapon?</span><hr size=1> 12/20 isn't good enough to taunt. How about, since Ragebringer is 15/25 and an easier quest, 14/20, no ac boosts since no other weapons have them. Oh, and make Rage of Tallon a permanent effect. <p>nillon<br>
